<DOC><DOCNO> AP901224-0055 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NY-12-24-90 1223EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Iran-Drugs     12-24 0151</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Iran-Drugs,0146</SECOND><HEAD>Iran Says It Arrests Thousands Of Drug Traffickers, Addicts</HEAD><DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   More than 1,900 alleged drug traffickersand 16,000 addicts were arrested in Iran in a five-week nationwidesweep, Tehran radio reported Monday.   The broadcast, monitored in Nicosia, quoted the Komiteh, theorganization responsible for internal security, as saying that morethan 1,653 pounds of various drugs were confiscated in thecrackdown. The radio said 57 guns and 80 vehicles also were seized.   Iranian law calls for a mandatory death sentence for possessionof drugs.   More than 1,500 people accused of drug trafficking have beenhanged in the past two years, and more than 100,000 people accusedof being addicts have been sent to hard labor camps.   Iranian opposition groups and independent human rightsorganizations claim the executions actually are carried out tocrush political opposition.</TEXT></DOC>